_Bangladesh Watchdog_
[informs](http://bangladeshwatchdog.blogspot.com/2010/08/bangladesh-made-boat-
reaches-france.html) that an ‘unsinkable eco-friendly’ boat made of jute fibre
has reached the coast of La Ciotat, South of France after an eight month long
journey from Bangladesh. The mission of the sail was to highlight the problems
Bangladeshi fishermen are facing due to global warming.

